trend_summary: Suburban district remained largely residential but saw incremental growth: highway widened, commercial pads added near the southern junction, and several cul-de-sac infills filled vacant green lots. Tree cover thinned along road edges and new builds, yet overall pattern stayed medium-density suburbia.
notable_changes: Interstate highway corridor widened with extra lanes and redesigned ramps.
New commercial/industrial roofs appear near the southwestern interchange.
Several cul-de-sac streets infilled with detached houses in central blocks.
Noticeable loss of tree canopy along expanded roads and new plots.
Small recreational/sports facility added northeast of the highway.
